title.narrative: 1.4 HEALTH SYSTEM STRENGHTENING

description.narrative: Output 1.4: By 2018, all levels of the health system, community structures and local authorities have strengthened capacities in planning and monitoring in accordance with equity- and gender-based approaches, in supply management (including supplies aimed at the prevention, detection and case management of HIV) and in logistics, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Health â€“ General, Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: Children under 5 years of age and pregnant women, particularly the most vulnerable, increasingly benefit from quality high-impact interventions for the prevention and management of maternal and childhood illnesses, including in emergency situations.
